cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR 

This paper deals with object recognition in images using unsupervised text corpora, which is a problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of language as a semantic basis also suggests that this paper could belong to natural language processing (cs.CL). The model proposed in the paper involves outlier detection and recognition models, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). Finally, the use of text corpora to understand objects in images could also be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR).
